OL,3,CFree speech law for universities being
OL,4,Crevived by government
OL,6,FThe government are reviving a
OL,7,Fcontroversial law aimed at protecting
OL,8,Ffree speech on university campuses.
OL,10,FThe Higher Education Freedom of Speech
OL,11,FAct was initially put forward by the
OL,12,FConservative government, and despite
OL,13,Fbeing shelved over concerns about
OL,14,Fstudent's welfare, it's now been given
OL,15,Fthe green light.
OL,17,FEducation Secretary Bridget Phillipson
OL,18,Fconfirmed on Wednesday "key
OL,19,Fprovisions" from the act will be
OL,20,Fbrought forward, but some aspects of
OL,21,Fthe bill have been dumped.
