OL,3,CFree speech law for universities being
OL,4,Crevived by government
OL,6,FHowever they are scrapping a
OL,7,F"statutory tort" that would've allowed
OL,8,Findividuals to sue universities and
OL,9,Fstudents' unions for breaching their
OL,10,Ffree speech duties.
OL,12,FThe government describe the tort as
OL,13,F"excessive and burdensome" with
OL,14,Fpotential to divert cash for students
OL,15,Ftoward "disproportionate and costly
OL,16,Flegal action from complaints".
OL,18,FSome of the duties placed on students'
OL,19,Funions are also being reversed, but
OL,20,Fthey will still be expected to
OL,21,F"protect lawful free speech".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
